  <prompt>
The SmartTodo Code Page has 22 test files written as "executable spec shims" — they LOOK like tests but don't actually run because vitest/jest isn't wired in `src/solutions/SmartTodo/package.json`. Per the no-shims principle: clean up.

Two options:
- (a) Wire vitest so the specs ARE real tests. Preferred — the specs exist as documented expectations and were written carefully.
- (b) Delete the dead test files. Simpler, but loses documented behavior.

This task = (a): wire vitest, fix any specs that don't pass (they likely DO pass, since they were written contemporaneously with the implementation), make `npm test` actually do something meaningful in `src/solutions/SmartTodo/`.

Reference: `src/solutions/CreateTodoWizard/package.json` already has vitest wired — copy the pattern.
  </prompt>

  <role>Frontend test infrastructure.</role>

  <goal>
1. Add vitest dependency + test script to `src/solutions/SmartTodo/package.json`.
2. Add `vitest.config.ts` (copy CreateTodoWizard's pattern).
3. Run `npm test` and fix any failing specs.
4. Wire to CI if not already covered by SDAP CI's general npm test sweep.
5. Document in `projects/smart-todo-r4/notes/lessons-learned.md` (R4-098) — "no shims = test runners must be wired before specs are written".
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="user feedback feedback_no-shims-clean-up-dead-code">No shims — wire the runner OR delete the specs. The current state (specs exist, runner doesn't) is the worst of both worlds.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CreateTodoWizard pattern">Copy CreateTodoWizard's vitest config — same package.json structure, same testing primitives. Don't invent new patterns.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check.</step>
    <step order="1">Compare `src/solutions/SmartTodo/package.json` vs `src/solutions/CreateTodoWizard/package.json` (which has vitest wired). List the deltas.</step>
    <step order="2">Add vitest dependency + script. Copy/adapt `vitest.config.ts`.</step>
    <step order="3">Run `npm test` and triage failures (likely 0 failures or trivial fixes since specs were written contemporaneously).</step>
    <step order="4">Verify CI picks up the new test runs.</step>
    <step order="5">Commit + PR.</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`cd src/solutions/SmartTodo && npm test` runs vitest and produces pass/fail output.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All previously-shim tests now actually execute (pass OR fail visibly, no silent skips).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">CI runs the new tests (or a follow-up task is filed to wire CI if separate).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
